\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 119. S. tenella} Wulfen in Jacq.,{\i  Collect. Bot. }{\b 3}: 144(1791). Leafy shoots 5-10 cm, procumbent, forming a rather dense mat. Leaves 10 × 1-2 mm, linear-subulate, aristate, with a narrow hyaline margin, usually ciliate, especially near the base. Flowering stem 5-15 cm, erect, slender, glabrous, with 2-8 flowers in a lax cyme. Petals 3 mm, creamy-white, obovate. 2n = 66.{\i  Shady rocks and screes; calcicole. • S.E. Alps.} Au It Ju.
