\pard\f0\fs28 Subsect.{\i  Tridactylites} (Haw.) Gornall. Erect annuals or biennials, more or less glandular-hairy. Leaves entire or shortly 3- to 5-lobed. Flowers small, on long pedicels, forming a lax, leafy panicle. Petals white (rarely yellowish or red), obtuse, truncate or slightly emarginate. Ovary almost completely inferior.
